body.description: Bring your dream nursery to life with the Graco Benton 5-in-1 Convertible Crib. With its timeless design, the Benton is the perfect addition to any nursery. The Benton is crafted from pine wood, engineered wood, and wood composites, and its applied finish has been tested to meet or exceed the applicable ASTM and CPSIA safety standards. The Benton is GREENGUARD Gold Certified and JPMA Certified. The Benton includes an adjustable mattress support base with 4 height options [note, this crib may only be used until your child can easily climb out or is taller than 35 inches (89 cm)]. The Benton can be converted from a crib to a toddler bed [Graco Toddler Safety Guardrail Kit (Slats) (01340-60 Series) sold separately], daybed, and full-size bed with headboard and optional footboard (full-size bed conversion kit sold separately). The Benton fits any standard full-size crib & toddler mattress (mattress sold separately –Graco crib mattress recommended). Graco is the recipient of the PTPA Seal of Approval and 2021-2023 Women's Choice Award for 9 out of 10 Recommended Baby & Kids Furniture. Backed by a 1-year limited manufacturer’s warranty. Assembly required. Mattress, toddler safety guardrail kit, and full-size bed conversion kit each sold separately.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 7, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Beautiful 5 in 1 crib. Very sturdy and easy to assemble. The best part is that it will accommodate your baby as itGrows. You can change the height of the mattress as needed. Turns into a youth. Trundle bed. Full size bed. It’s great and the price was adorable as well. I highly recommend this Product for new parents. You cannotGo wrong.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 11, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This crib is nice. I like the fact that it's a 5 in 1 and it kinda "grows" with the baby, per say. It's sturdy. It's worth the money. I like that you have different colors to choose from.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 29, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars The perfect crib
reviews.reviewText: This crib was very straightforward with its directions as long as you pay attention to detail. Including the pictures, as they will show you sticker details on the pieces to determine which direction to face them etc. the only struggle we had was putting the base inside for the mattress, it was very hard to pull the crib tight enough to fit in all the holes, but with my experience in the past it seems to be just a crib thing, not necessarily this crib only. It’s extremely sturdy and not heavy to move either. I love the table and drawer feature on it, allows us to have more with limited wall space in a small room. Also the dividers between drawers and under the changing table were a little tricky to set in place while assembled, but not impossible. Need 2 people at least.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 12, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for the price!
reviews.reviewText: After reading the other reviews I was hesitant about this crib but it’s great! The shipping was fast and it came in perfect condition. The box was a little beat up with some holes but it’s VERY heavy so I’m sure it’s hard for the delivery drivers who are alone to move it. The crib pieces were protected enough that there was no damage to any of the paint or pieces.Assembly:The instructions were pretty clear and easy to follow. It took my husband and I a few hours to put together. I would rate the difficulty 3/5, you may yell at the crib but it won’t ruin your marriage lol. The harder part was the changing table and aligning the divider boards. Everything lined up great for us! A lot of the pieces look almost identical but they have subtle differences so you have to pay attention to the numbers, I am assuming that’s why a lot of the reviews say it doesn’t line up. My husbands only issue was the way they package the hardware makes it hard to keep it organized since all the screws look very similar and they move all about when trying to get others out.Size:I was worried from the reviews about the changing table being small but it’s a very normal size if not big. I am not worried about my baby not fitting on it even into toddler years. The top mattress height seems a little low to me but this is my first baby so my perceptions may be off, and it’s not astronomically low anyway.Overall we are very happy with this crib it looks great and works great! All the drawers fit perfect and open/close with no issue. I would recommend this crib especially for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 11, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Spacious and versatile
reviews.reviewText: Overall, this is a great crib. It comes with a fairly affordable price tag, and is what you would expect from its description. The drawers, shelves and changing table are so convenient and smart. I would have given 5 stars however when my partner and I were building it one of the wood supports for the drawers shattered. Customer service was slightly difficult to get ahold of and it took us awhile to get a replacement. However they eventually did get back to us and were helpful. Everything worked out! The drawers don’t perfectly align but that’s only really aesthetic issue if anything. They still open and close just fine. I am content with my purchase and the crib looks lovely in our nursery. Our little girl will love it and I’m excited that it can potentially be used for years!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Definitely Grows with your Toddler !
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this back in 2016 for my son and Loved it ! We used it up until he could no longer fit it even after toddler years . It is sturdy , and easy to put together .

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I purchased this for my daughter, who is expecting her first baby. The crib arrived on time and was easy to assemble. It looks super cute as well! Would definitely purchase again.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The crib is super cute and lightweight. Everything came in good condition and I like how the tools were packaged separately. I will suggest having two people put it together, and it can be time consuming to do; it took my mom & me well over an hour. But I love it and the color (I got it in pebble gray), can't wait to see my baby girl in it soon 💜 definitely recommend.
This was a gift, so I don't really have anything to offer.
